{
 "name": "RPlog_Capture_Of_A_Marine",
 "title": "Capture of a Marine",
 "summary": "At Coronet City Spaceport on Corellia, the mercenary marine Vengan and his crew run an extraction, covering a black-clad intel officer fleeing CorSec guards toward their shuttle Valiant. In the chaos Vengan is grazed, knocked from the ramp, and left behind as the shuttle escapes, then knocked unconscious and hauled off to the office of CorSec Colonel Twila Virda, the Twi'lek he had once met on Coruscant. Behind closed doors Twila reveals herself, tends his wounds, and stages the sounds of a beating for the surveillance, torn between her duty and her clear affection for him. The two spar verbally as she interrogates him: she even hands him her own blaster to prove she means no harm, and Vengan insists he was simply hired by the Republic to pick someone up on Corellia and knew nothing more. After a bluffed threat with a tampered med droid extracts what little he knows, Twila strikes a deal, freeing Vengan in exchange for delivering a warning to his employers that smuggling through Corellia will not be easy. She escorts him to the terminal, slips him a coded contact cylinder and a furtive kiss, and Vengan boards a shuttle off-world.",
